---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About — Digital PR Agency for Higher Education"
  description="701am is a digital PR agency for higher education. Built by a team that spent 20 years in education visibility — now helping institutions get earned media that compounds."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <header class="about-hero">
    <div class="hero-atmos"><div class="grid"></div><div class="glow g1"></div><div class="glow g2"></div><div class="glow g3"></div></div>
    <div class="wrap" style="position:relative;z-index:1">
      <div class="eyebrow">About 701am</div>
      <h1>We spent 20 years doing <em class="grad">earned media by hand</em>. <br>Now we do it for clients.</h1>
      <p class="lede">After two decades building and operating education visibility properties that millions of prospective students used to compare programs, we started 701am to do for institutions what we used to do for ourselves — earned media that compounds.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- STORY -->
  <article class="about-prose">
    <div class="seg">Where we started</div>
    <p class="big">We've spent two decades on one question: when someone is choosing a school, how do they decide — and how do you make sure your program is in that decision?</p>
    <p>We were part of the teams that built and operated a network of education properties — <strong>CollegeChoice</strong>, <strong>TheBestSchools</strong>, <strong>CollegeConsensus</strong>, <strong>BestCollegeReviews</strong>, <strong>ValueColleges</strong>, and hundreds more — that millions of prospective students used to compare programs. We understood exactly how applicants research, what makes a program credible, and how to put the right institutions in front of the right students at the moment they were deciding.</p>
    <p>That's not adjacent experience. That's <em>the job</em>. We just spent twenty years doing it manually, site by site, before the technology existed to help institutions do it for themselves.</p>

    <div class="seg">The ground moved</div>
    <p>A few years ago, the behavior we'd built a career around started to change. Applicants stopped beginning with a Google search and a comparison site. They started asking an AI assistant — <em>"what's the best online MSW for working adults?"</em> — and taking the short, confident answer it gave them. They discovered programs through press coverage and thought leadership, in channels that didn't exist a decade ago.</p>
    <p class="pull">The decision was forming somewhere most institutions couldn't see — or optimize for.</p>
    <p>We watched institutions that had spent years and fortunes on their visibility quietly disappear from the places applicants were looking. Not because their programs got worse — because the place the decision happened moved, and the old playbooks couldn't follow.</p>

    <div class="seg">Why 701am exists</div>
    <p>The signals that make a program credible haven't actually changed. Rankings. Real outcomes data. Coverage in publications people trust. Those still decide who gets shortlisted — it's just that <strong>an AI reads them now too</strong>, alongside the humans. The work that earns those signals is the same work we've done for two decades. It's just slow, manual, and expensive when done by a traditional agency — which is why most institutions only do it in bursts, around a campaign, and then let it reset.</p>
    <p>701am is the agency we wish had existed: a digital PR firm purpose-built for higher education, that earns media coverage continuously across every channel that matters — so a school's visibility compounds instead of resetting, and so it shows up in the AI answer, the search result, and the press, all at once.</p>
    <p class="pull">We're not a PR firm that discovered higher ed. We're education-visibility operators who spent two decades on this exact problem — now serving the institutions that need it.</p>
  </article>

  <!-- CREDENTIALS -->
  <section class="creds">
    <div class="atmos"><div class="dg dg1"></div></div>
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ch">
          <div class="eb">The track record</div>
          <h2>Not a first attempt at education visibility.</h2>
          <p>We came from the trenches, and the numbers prove it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="creds-grid">
          <div class="cred"><div class="cv">20+</div><div class="cl">Years in education visibility and media</div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cv">Hundreds</div><div class="cl">Of education properties built and operated</div></div>
          <div class="cred"><div class="cv">Millions</div><div class="cl">Of prospective student interactions across that network</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE'VE BUILT -->
  <section class="past">
    <div class="ph">
      <div class="eb">Built & operated</div>
      <h2>A network applicants actually used.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="past-list">
      <span class="pl">CollegeChoice</span>
      <span class="pl">TheBestSchools</span>
      <span class="pl">CollegeConsensus</span>
      <span class="pl">BestCollegeReviews</span>
      <span class="pl">ValueColleges</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- VALUES -->
  <section class="values">
    <div class="value">
      <i class="ti ti-shield-check"></i>
      <div><h3>Earned, never faked</h3><p>No fabricated coverage, no invented quotes, no manufactured rankings. Earned media only works if it's actually earned — and in higher ed, anything less is a liability.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="value">
      <i class="ti ti-arrows-up-right"></i>
      <div><h3>Coverage should compound</h3><p>The old model resets every campaign. We build so every placement makes the next one easier — visibility as an asset, not a recurring expense.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="value">
      <i class="ti ti-focus-2"></i>
      <div><h3>One world, done deeply</h3><p>We don't serve every industry. We serve higher ed — because depth beats breadth, and because it's the world we've lived in for twenty years.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICES PREVIEW -->
  <section class="band wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <div class="sec-eyebrow">What we do</div>
      <h2>Earned media for <em class="grad">higher education</em>.</h2>
      <p>Every engagement is scoped to deliver a specific number of placements — up to 50 per campaign. No long-term retainers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pricing-cmp" style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto">
      <div class="pcard">
        <div class="pc-head">
          <div class="pc-icon" style="background:var(--amber-soft);color:var(--amber-deep)"><i class="ti ti-calendar"></i></div>
          <div>
            <div class="pc-label">Earned Media Session</div>
            <div class="pc-sub">90-minute strategy session</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pc-price">
          <span class="pc-amt">$500</span>
          <span class="pc-per">one-time</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="pc-feat">
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>Data audit & story identification</li>
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>Reporter list for top 3 angles</li>
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>No obligation to continue</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="pcard pcard-701">
        <div class="pc-head">
          <div class="pc-icon pc-icon-grad"><i class="ti ti-rocket"></i></div>
          <div>
            <div class="pc-label" style="color:#fff">Earned Media Engagement</div>
            <div class="pc-sub" style="color:var(--night-txt)">Up to 50 placements</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pc-price">
          <span class="pc-amt pc-amt-grad">$6,500</span>
          <span class="pc-per" style="color:var(--night-txt)">per engagement</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="pc-feat pc-feat-dark">
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>Full campaign — research, pitches, outreach</li>
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>Up to 50 placements</li>
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>AI citation tracking</li>
          <li><i class="ti ti-check"></i>No long-term contract</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CLOSING -->
  <section class="closing">
    <div class="catmos"><div class="cg"></div></div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="pill-badge"><span class="tagm">Filed at sunrise</span></div>
      <h2>Let's get your institution <em class="grad">covered</em>.</h2>
      <p>Start with a $500 Earned Media Session — or book a discovery call to scope your campaign.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"><i class="ti ti-calendar"></i>Book a discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>